p.span: The following system trades were identified by the group based on design experience with similar technologies, published specifications and costs for likely components considered, and the laws of physics. Generally, higher performance, longer maintenance intervals and a higher precision and quality means additional
costs; however, sometimes the high initial cost can be offset by total ownership costs. Actual design and component selection will be based on satisfying customer requirements.
